-- Mandela Memorial May Be Held at Westminster Abbey: Independent
-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 2013-06-30T09:54:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-30/mandela-memorial-may-be-held-at-westminster-abbey-independent.html
Service for  Nelson Mandela  at
Westminster Abbey, which Queen Elizabeth II has requested to
attend should South Africa agree, would be first for non-British
citizen, Johannesburg’s Sunday Independent reports.
* Discussions have been held between Westminster Abbey and South
African High Commission officials, Sunday Independent cites
church’s head of communications, Duncan Jeffrey, as saying
* Buckingham Palace, South Africa’s International Relations
Ministry declined to comment: Independent
* NOTE: Mandela, 94, South Africa’s first black president, has
been hospitalized since June 8 after contracting lung infection  To contact the reporter on this story:
